properties.description: Growing as individual trees or small groups, this species of walnut tree is found by mountain river banks. The walnuts are boiled and the liquid is drunk to treat cardiac diseases (high blood pressure), and to rinse the mouth against gum disease. An ointment is made from the juice of the fruit husk to treat ulcers and skin diseases like eczema. The bark of the roots are used to create a very mild laxative.
